# virt-sparsify

> Make virtual machine drive images thin-provisioned
> Use only for offline machines to avoid data corruption
> More information: https://libguestfs.org

- Create a sparsified compressed image without snapshots from an unsparsified one:

`virt-sparsify --compress {string value: path/to/image.qcow2} {string value: path/to/image_new.qcow2}`

- Sparsify an image in-place:

`virt-sparsify --in-place {string value: path/to/image.img}`
